.
 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{T}$
\end_inset

 is a subgraph of 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{G}$
\end_inset

 (with the same weights on the edges), so 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{T}\preceq L_{G}$
\end_inset

 (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Spielman2009a"

\end_inset

 for example for a proof of this fact).
 Furthermore, we have 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{T}\preceq\text{st}_{G}\left(T\right)L_{G}$
\end_inset

.
 This latter inequality is result of Boman and Hendrickson 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
